<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/main_only"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">
  <div class="top-portlet">
    <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">
      <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
        <p>
          Examine the project's overview tab first, then examine if the
          project is using code, bugs, etc.... <strong>Mark the project
          reviewed now</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          Does the project appear to be legitimate? Are its licenses simple
          and clearly open and free? <strong>Mark the project approved
          now</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          If the project appears legitimate, yet incomplete, that is fine.
          Approve the project, consider sending a request to ask the owner to
          update his project with more details because it will help him
          get contributors.
        </p>

        <p>
          There are a few reasons you may want to <strong>withhold
          approval</strong>, and you should contact the project owner if
          you do.
        </p>

        <ul class="bulleted">
          <li>
            The project has no license.
          </li>
          <li>
            The project has only Other/Open source selected as a license and
            the license info field does not contain a URL to a license, or
            contains the whole license
          </li>
          <li>
            The Other/Open source license appears to discriminate against who
            or how the project's work is used.
          </li>
          <li>
            The project is too vague to know if it is legitimate.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          If the project looks like a test, a prank, or spam,
          <strong>deactivate it</strong>.
        </p>

      <input type="hidden" name="next_url"
        tal:attributes="value view/next_url" />
      <table class="listing" id="license-listing">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Licenses</th>
            <th>Description of additional licenses</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td style="white-space: nowrap">
              <tal:licenses repeat="license context/licenses">
                <tal:license tal:replace="license/title">
                  GPL
                </tal:license>
                <br/>
              </tal:licenses>
              <tal:none condition="not:context/licenses">None specified
              </tal:none>
            </td>
            <td tal:content="structure context/license_info/fmt:text-to-html"/>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <tal:menu replace="structure view/@@+related-pages" />
</div>

</body>
</html>
